Vice President Kamala Harris and Second Gentleman Douglas Emhoff will be embarking on a trip to Ghana, Tanzania, and Zambia from March 25 to April 2. This visit will follow the U.S.-Africa Leaders Summit hosted by President Biden in December 2022 and aims to strengthen partnerships between the United States and Africa. The Vice President will focus on areas such as security, economic prosperity, digital economy, climate adaptation, resilience, business ties, and investment. She will meet with the presidents of Ghana, Tanzania, and Zambia to discuss regional and global priorities, including democracy, economic growth, food security, and the situation in Ukraine. Additionally, the Vice President will engage with civil society, including young leaders, business representatives, entrepreneurs, and members of the African Diaspora, in order to strengthen people-to-people ties.